Data Overview 2


Data Source:
The data used for this analysis was sourced from Kaggle.com
Key Metrics




System Architecture:
The project workflow involves analyzing Healthcare data to identify trends and contributing factors, gathering relevant data from Kaggles.com , cleansing and preprocessing the dataset, applying machine learning models to predict accident severity, performing in-depth analysis using DAX and Power BI, visualizing key insights through interactive dashboards, and providing data-driven recommendations to improve road safety and reduce accident severity.




Data Features
The dataset includes key metrics such as Patient ID, Treatment Date, Recovery Status, and Length of Stay, each represented with clear and intuitive icons for quick comprehension. Additionally, the section includes a 'Data Dictionary' that visually outlines the relationships between important data attributes such as Insurance Type, Treatment Cost, and Recovery Probability, highlighting crucial factors like Age and Diagnosis, which are essential for analyzing patient outcomes and healthcare performance trends.
